'''Marcello Cestaro''' (born 1938)  is an [[Italy|Italian]] [[businessman]]<ref>{{cite news |title=Marcello Cestaro cittadino onorario di Padova |url=http://www.padova24ore.it/succede-in-comune/2587-marcello-cestaro-cittadino-onorario-di-padova.html |work=Padova24ore |date=26 February 2010 |accessdate=27 January 2012 }}</ref> and the current owner and chairman of Serie A1 [[women's basketball]] club [[PF Schio|Pallacanestro Femminile Schio]].<ref>{{cite news |title=Organigramma Famila Schio |url=http://www.familabasket.it/category/societa/ |work=Famila Schio |date=30 January 2012 |accessdate=30 January 2012 }}</ref> He is a native of [[Schio]], [[Province of Vicenza|Vicenza]], Italy.<ref>{{cite news |title=Marcello Cestaro |url=http://www.cavalieridellavoro.it/cavaliere.php?numero_brevetto=2435 |work=Federazione Nazionale dei Cavalieri del Lavoro |date=30 January 2012 |accessdate=30 January 2012 }}</ref> Until June 2013, he was also owner and chairman of [[Serie B]] club [[Calcio Padova]].<ref>{{cite news |title=UFFICIALE Il Padova annuncia Penocchio Presidente |url=http://www.padovasport.tv/tutto-padova/ufficiale-il-padova-annuncia-penocchio-presidente-7938 |work=Padova Sport|date=28 June 2013 |accessdate=8 July 2013 }}</ref>

Cestaro has business interest in [[supermarket]] and [[hypermarket]], with the brands ''Famila'', ''Emisfero'', ''A&O'' and ''Cash and Carry'' managed by his company ''Unicomm Srl''. He entered into [[football (soccer)|football]] in 2004, detecting the [[Calcio Padova]] militant at time in [[Lega Pro Prima Divisione|Series C1]]. Since 1986, he has also been the owner of Pallacanestro Femminile Schio.

