'''Martin Saarikangas''' (born 24 January 1937) is a Finnish [[shipbuilder]], best known as the founder of Masa-Yards (now [[Aker Finnyards]]), after the bankruptcy of [[Wärtsilä Marine]]. From 2003 to 2007 he was a member of the [[Parliament of Finland|Finnish Parliament]]. In 1994 he played three minutes for [[Veikkausliiga|Finnish association football top flight]] side [[Turun Palloseura|TPS Turku]] at the age of 57.

